Edge}}\n}}\n|}\n\n===Evolution===\n{{evobox-3\n|pictype=art\n|type1=Rock\n|no1=524\n|name1=Roggenrola\n|type1-1=Rock\n|evo1={{bag|Rare Candy}}<br>{{color2|000|Level|Level 25}}\n|no2=525\n|name2=Boldore\n|type1-2=Rock\n|evo2={{bag|Pal Pad}}<br>{{color2|000|Trade}}\n|no3=526\n|name3=Gigalith\n|type1-3=Rock\n}}\n\n===Sprites===\n{{Spritebox/Header|type=Rock}}\n{{Spritebox/NA|gen=V}}\n{{Spritebox/5|ndex=525}}\n{{Spritebox/6|ndex=525}}\n{{Spritebox/7|ndex=525}}\n{{Spritebox/Footer|525|Boldore}}\n\n==Trivia==\n* Boldore is very similar to {{p|Graveler}}. Both are Rock-type Pokémon introduced in an odd-numbered generation with a base stat total of 390 that evolved at level 25 and can evolve again by [[trade|trading]].\n\n===Origin===\nBoldore appears to be based on a {{wp|geode}}. It also has some aspects of a {{wp|crab}}.\n\n====Name origin====\nBoldore may be combination of \'\'boulder\'\' and \'\'ore\'\'. It may also derive from \'\'bold\'\' (outstanding or large).\n\nGantle may be a combination of 岩 \'\'gan\'\' (rock) and \'\'{{wp|mantle (geology)|mantle}}\'\'.\n\n==In other languages==\n{{Other languages|type=Rock|type2=Rock\n|ja=ガントル \'\'Gantle\'\'|jameaning=From {{tt|岩 \'\'gan\'\'|rock}} and \'\'mantle\'\'\n|de=Sedimantur|demeaning=From \'\'Sediment\'\'\n|fr=Géolithe|frmeaning=From \'\'geo\'\' and \'\'lithe\'\'\n|es=Boldore|esmeaning=Same as English name\n|it=Boldore|itmeaning=Same as English name\n|ko=암트르 \'\'Amtru\'\'|komeaning=From {{tt|암(巖) \'\'am\'\'|rock}} and \'\'mantle\'\'\n|zh_cmn=地幔岩 \'\'Dìmànyán\'\'|zh_cmnmeaning=From {{tt|地幔 \'\'dìmàn\'\'|mantle}} and {{tt|岩 \'\'yán\'\'|boulder}}.\n|ru=Болдор \'\'Boldor\'\'|rumeaning=Transcription of English name\n}}\n<br clear="left">\n\n==Related articles==\n* [[Ash\'s Boldore]]\n<!--\n==Notes==\n<references />-->\n\n==External links==\n\n{{-}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Rock}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Rock|prevnum=524|prev=Roggenrola|nextnum=526|next=Gigalith}}\n|}\n{{Project Pokédex notice}}\n\n[[Category:Po